				<span class="name">Mostafa Karimian-Eghbal</span>
				<span class="cv">Mostafa has a BSc in Soil Science from the California Polytechnic State University and an MSc and PhD in Soil Science from The University of California, Davis. Mostafa was Deputy Minister of Technology in the Ministry of Science, Research and Technology in President Khatami's Cabinet. Prior to that, he was the President of the Isfahan Science and Technology Town. He is presently Associate Professor at Tarbiat Modares University. His fields of interest include Science and Technology Parks. He is widely published in the field of Incubator and Science Park Management.</span>
				<span class="name">Roshanak Khalili-Dwyer</span>
				<span class="cv">Roshanak has a BA in East Asian Studies and Political Science from Connecticut College, holds a Master's Degree in International Relations from Columbia University and an MSc from the London Business School Sloan Fellowship Programme. She is advisor to the Board of Directors of Butane Industrial Group. She has further experience in finance through her seven-year tenure at Bankers Trust both in New York and London. Roshanak currently serves as director for the Institute for Family Business UK and is a member of the London Business School UK Regional Advisory Board. She is a member of the Board of Directors of the Iran Heritage Foundation.</span>
				<span class="name">Mohit Mamudi</span>
				<span class="cv">Mohit has worked as a management and marketing executive or consultant with more than 20 Fortune 500 corporations in Europe, China, Latin America, and MENA region. He runs a strategic consultancy business and is a board member of other companies. As an MBA alumnus of Boston University, he acts as international development advisor to the university. He frequently speaks in conferences and has lectured in postgraduate and management training programmes in the UK, USA, Iran, Egypt and Russia. He is a founder and director of the Centre for Development Management Studies (CEDEMAS), and has designed and conducted management training programmes throughout Europe, the Middle East and Asia.</span>
				<span class="name">Reza Moradi (Project Managing Director)</span>
				<span class="cv">Reza has a BSc and an MSc from Isfahan University of Technology in Engineering. He is the founder of the Iron and Steel Society of Iran and the founder of Iran's first technology incubator, Qadir. He also founded Sheikh Bahaee Technology Park in Isfahan. In addition, he was the Vice President for Executive Affairs of Isfahan Science &amp; Technology town. He was also the Secretary of the 7th National Economic Development Congress, held in Iran to study the relations between government, industry and universities they pertain to economic development. He has taught several university level courses and is widely published in the field of Incubator and Science Park Management.</span>
				<span class="name">Ramin Navvabpour</span>
				<span class="cv">Ramin Navvabpour is presently the Managing Director of the Institute for Knowledge and Technology Development, a training and consultancy firm focused on enabling companies and entrepreneurs from the Iranian public and private sector. Prior to that, Ramin was the Head of the Information Technology Research Department at the Academic Centre for Education and Research (ACER), an affiliation of the Sharif University of Technology. He was also the Vice President of "Rooyesh ICT Incubator". In addition, he has held positions as senior consultant to some of Iran's most prevailing public and private organisations and is a leading figure in the establishment and promotion of pioneering management techniques, particularly pertaining to the private sector. He is a software engineer by training and is currently studying for a Master's Degree in Business Management at Tehran University.</span>
				<span class="name">Alieh Ashtari (Project Director)</span>
				<span class="cv">Alieh has an MSc in Engineering from Isfahan University of Technology. She has established two successful businesses and worked as Managing Director in those companies for over 10 years. She was a member of the Board of Directors of Isfahan Venture Capital Fund, as well as an active member of the Isfahan Provincial Think-Tank Centre. Additionally, she was a project member in the 'infoDev Programme', a global development programme within the World Bank. Prior to that, Alieh was teaching at university level.</span>
